oai_dc:dc.dc:title: A. F. A. Visits A Member's Aviaries
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: n/a, n/a
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Situated on a hillside facing East inthe Echo Park area of Los Angeles, DaveShupert has turned a fifty foot by twohundred foot lot into a serene setting mixingaviaries with a forest of pines,avocados, and elm.Dave came to California in 1959 fromChicago, where he developed his interestin birds more than twenty years ago . Hisfirst efforts were devoted to Cockatiels,but today he has a striking assortment offmches, psittacines, doves, pheasants, andturkeys.
